short-description: The perfect upgrade for your connection between your thermostat and cylinder head. Designed using durable silicone and billet aluminum to greatly outlast the OE rubber and plastic combination. Some of the weakest points of the cooling systems in BMW's can come down to the OE plastic fittings breaking down from the constant changes in temperature, softening these plastic components. When this happens, even simply moving the hose slightly could cause the fitting to crack, causing the coolant to leak all over. The ECS design silicone hose with billet aluminum adapter retains OE fitment with superior strength to not only handle the performance, but also stand up to the wear and tear of a daily driver. Features: Manufactured from billet 6061-T6 and type III anodized for exceptional durability and corrosion resistance. Much stronger part than OEM plastic Will not become brittle and fatigue over time due to thermal cycling. This will prevent the part from breaking during removal and re-installation. Constructed of 4-Ply reinforced silicone for improved durability over the failure-prone OE rubber hose. Flourosilicone lined internal layer for exceptional chemical resistance. Silicone offers reduced thermal conductivity as well as improved resistance to ozone and UV degradation for improved performance and durability. Follows OEM form for perfect fitment. Utilizes OEM O-ring 11537545278 to ensure a proper seal. Replaces Genuine BMW Part Number: 11537545890

cleanDesc: ECS Performance Coolant Outlet Hose Kit - E60 E61 N52
short-description: The perfect upgrade for your connection between your thermostat and cylinder head. Designed using durable silicone and billet aluminum to greatly outlast the OE rubber and plastic combination. Some of the weakest points of the cooling systems in BMW's can come down to the OE plastic fittings breaking down from the constant changes in temperature, softening these plastic components. When this happens, even simply moving the hose slightly could cause the fitting to crack, causing the coolant to leak all over. The ECS design silicone hose with billet aluminum adapter retains OE fitment with superior strength to not only handle the performance, but also stand up to the wear and tear of a daily driver. Features: Manufactured from billet 6061-T6 and type III anodized for exceptional durability and corrosion resistance. Much stronger part than OEM plastic Will not become brittle and fatigue over time due to thermal cycling. This will prevent the part from breaking during removal and re-installation. Constructed of 4-Ply reinforced silicone for improved durability over the failure-prone OE rubber hose. Flourosilicone lined internal layer for exceptional chemical resistance. Silicone offers reduced thermal conductivity as well as improved resistance to ozone and UV degradation for improved performance and durability. Follows OEM form for perfect fitment. Utilizes OEM O-ring 11537545278 to ensure a proper seal. Replaces Genuine BMW Part Number: 11537544638

N62 Engine Collapsible Cooling Pipe - E60 E63 E65 E53 E70
short-description: Has your BMW's with the N62 V8 engine developed a coolant leak at the front of the engine from the timing cover weep hole? If so the it is likely that the coolant transfer pipe seal, located below the intake manifold has developed a leak. Normally, replacing the seal on this pipe would require almost 40 hours of labor and involve removing the entire engine from the car, then removing the cylinder heads, and timing covers. With this new collapsible pipe this repair can be accomplished in under 10 hours! Transmission Cooler Hose Set - E39 540i 99-03, E38 740i/iL 99-01
  ...
short-description: The oil cooler/heat exchanger for the automatic transmission is one of the most overlooked sections of the 540i and 740i cooling system. The cooler (heat exchanger) is a part of the overall cooling system and uses coolant circulated from the regular cooling system to cool the transmission oil running through this small cooling block. Some of the hoses are shared with the rest of the cooling system as well. The E38/E39 heat exchanger is located along the driver's side frame rail and is accessed from the wheel well. We recommend servicing or cleaning the heat exchanger along with any cooling system overhaul. Or if you're having transmission faults (especially for temperature) you may want to clean the transmission cooler anyway and these hoses will be a nice finishing touch.   Replacing or cleaning the heat exchanger components could lead to better shifting of the automatic as the cooler itself can become clogged. If you're experiencing harder or hesitating shifts, and the internal transmission temperature is rising without being regulated, the components in this system are the likely cause. Staying on top of the cooling needs of the transmission will help prevent a very costly transmission repair in the future. These hoses are easily replaced and you can clean the heat exchanger easily with brake cleaner and some brushes.   Included in this handy package are:

cleanDesc: E46 M3 Samco Silicone Hose Set
short-description: Replace your BMW's ordinary and failure-prone rubber radiator hoses with this set of high performance Samco Sport silicone hoses, the clear first choice for competitive race and aggressive street BMWs. Samco Sport hose kits have been designed as direct replacement to original equipment hoses for use in both motorsport and high performance street / road use. Samco's silicone hose material is able to withstand much higher temperatures and pressures than standard hoses, giving your BMW both high reliability and superior performance under all conditions. These hoses are frequently used in motorsports and forced induction turbo and supercharger setups for their ability to perform under extreme conditions, and are ideal for any BMW where reliability is a must. To ensure absolute quality, Samco only uses premium quality silicone rubber and all of the hoses are hand finished and inspected by race equipment engineers. Choose from multiple color options to personalize your engine compartment.   E46 M3 Samco Silicone Hose Set includes:  upper radiator hose to thermostat (11537830716)  lower radiator hose to thermostat (11537830715)  expansion tank return hose (11537830713)   Fitment note: the silicone hoses replace the rubber hose section of the stock coolant hoses. The plastic connectors on the original hose must be transferred over to the new silicone hose. New hose clamps are recommended.     2001-2006    M3

MINI R56 Cooper S Samco Silicone Hose Set
short-description: Replace your MINI's ordinary and failure-prone rubber radiator hoses with this set of high performance Samco Sport silicone hoses, the clear first choice for competitive race and aggressive street BMWs. Samco Sport hose kits have been designed as direct replacement to original equipment hoses for use in both motorsport and high performance street / road use. Samco's silicone hose material is able to withstand much higher temperatures and pressures than standard hoses, giving your MINI both high reliability and superior performance under all conditions. These hoses are frequently used in motorsports and forced induction turbo and supercharger setups for their ability to perform under extreme conditions, and are ideal for any MINI where reliability is a must. To ensure absolute quality, Samco only uses premium quality silicone rubber and all of the hoses are hand finished and inspected by race equipment engineers.      2007-2013    MINI Cooper S
